The paper deals with the design of functionals for ranking joint probability distributions based on their correlations, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the Principle of Constant Correlations, which is a concept commonly used in machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions inferential transformations and variable mappings, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses notions of statistical sufficiency, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
